      "writtenOn": "2019-06-25T22:05:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If these used width() and height(), the only reason this needs to be friendly is for the writable glyph.fImage pointer without checks, correct? At this point can we just pass a non-const SkGlyph into this and have a non-const \u0027image()\u0027. Then we can pass the non-const version into the scaler context and always provide the const versions to the outside world to separate the inside from the outside? Then we wouldn\u0027t even need all the friends. We could even pass a const SkGlyph here but also pass in a non-const pointer to the dst (which might be the same pointer fImage is set to... or not as the case may be).",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 1292,
        "startChar": 28,
        "endLine": 1292,
        "endChar": 34
      },
